metadata.name: Dogsimo di Giovanni de' Medici
metadata.description:
Dogsimo di Giovanni de' Medici (27 Sept 1389 - 1 Aug 1464) - Lord of Pups
Dogsimo established the Medici family as effective rulers of the dog park during the Doggie Renaissance. He was named Alpha of the Pack of Pups, following that acting as an ambassador for dogs, demonstrating a renowned loyalty. The dog bone, issued by the Medici bank, became the preferred treat for pups throughout the park during Dogsimo’s prime.
He expanded the family's interests into dog toys significantly with > 600,000 dog bones, ~$500 million inflation adjusted, on toys, learning, architecture & culture. Including Dogatello’s Barkid, the first freestanding dog sculpture since antiquity.
Dogsimo’s collar is said to carry an ancient secret around a ball + 3 character symbol. As the Medici ball on their coat of arms, has a hidden meaning representing treats. Dogsimo was a dog of many secrets, with some still yet to be revealed soon.
